  "body": "![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/498913/93107453-846f1600-f6a9-11ea-9c26-600e6f95a637.png)\r\n\r\nTransactions in a block during the fast sync have no SenderAddress recovered (very expensive operation) so the ContractAddress is having null passed as the sender and stores the contract addresses incorrectly.\r\n\r\nSame when serving requests for unrecovered receipts.\r\n\r\nAlso in calls in this form:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/498913/93107668-d3b54680-f6a9-11ea-9a06-c607a04ef345.png)\r\n\r\nseem to be inefficient because they recover data for the whole block just to return one transaction (which is very expensive if we take into account a necessity or recovering the sender from the signature)\r\n",
